
[1]preventive

   PREVENT'IVE, a. Tending to hinder; hindering the access of; as a
   medicine preventive of disease.

   PREVENT'IVE, n. That which prevents; that which intercepts the access
   or approach of. Temperance and exercise are excellent preventives of
   debility and languor.

   1. An antidote previously taken. A medicine may be taken as a
   preventive of disease.
